President Trump held a press conference at the NATO headquarters in Brussels, where he discussed the progress made during the NATO summit. He emphasized that the United States has been paying a disproportionate amount for NATO and that other countries need to increase their contributions. He stated that many countries have committed to increasing their defense spending and that an additional $33 billion has been raised. Trump also expressed hope for improved relations with Russia and mentioned his upcoming meeting with President Putin. He answered questions from various reporters on topics such as his threat to pull out of NATO, his views on Russia, his expectations for the Putin meeting, and his thoughts on Brexit. Overall, Trump highlighted the progress made at the NATO summit and expressed optimism for future developments.